00:02:25.820 --> 00:02:29.660
FFmpeg is an open source
software system that is

00:02:30.020 --> 00:02:33.450
the invisible backbone behind
YouTube, Netflix, Chrome,

00:02:33.540 --> 00:02:37.360
VLC, Discord, and basically
every platform that

00:02:37.460 --> 00:02:40.620
touches video or audio on the internet.

00:02:41.520 --> 00:02:45.420
It can decode, encode,
transcode, stream, and

00:02:45.480 --> 00:02:49.080
play almost any video or audio format ever

00:02:49.160 --> 00:02:53.100
created. To me, it is one of
the most incredible software

00:02:53.120 --> 00:02:58.400
systems ever developed, and
it's all done by volunteers.

00:02:59.240 --> 00:03:03.160
VLC is also a legendary
piece of software. It is an

00:03:03.200 --> 00:03:07.040
open source media player that plays
basically anything you throw at

00:03:07.100 --> 00:03:11.060
it, any format, any platform,
no ads, no tracking.

00:03:11.600 --> 00:03:15.000
It has been downloaded over
six billion times, and

00:03:15.040 --> 00:03:18.460
again, for me, it has been
one of my favorite pieces of

00:03:18.560 --> 00:03:22.440
software ever, with the most
legendary logo, which I,

00:03:22.500 --> 00:03:26.720
of course, had to honor in this
conversation by wearing the

00:03:27.660 --> 00:03:30.810
VLC traffic cone hat the whole time.

00:03:31.840 --> 00:03:35.320
So again, above all else, thank
you to the incredible volunteer

00:03:35.380 --> 00:03:39.200
engineers who put their heart and
soul into this code that has been

00:03:39.220 --> 00:03:42.800
used and loved by billions
of people. Thank you.

00:03:43.920 --> 00:03:49.180
And about the two great engineers and human
beings I'm talking to in this episode,

00:03:50.080 --> 00:03:54.060
Jean-Baptiste is the
president of VideoLAN and

00:03:54.140 --> 00:04:01.720
