00:36:51.576 --> 00:36:57.076
source element? So when we say what is
FFmpeg, it's an open source project.

00:36:57.296 --> 00:37:01.216
- Yeah. So FFmpeg, VLC,
x264, VideoLAN, everything

00:37:01.256 --> 00:37:04.936
we do is fully open source. And for the
people who don't understand how open

00:37:05.016 --> 00:37:08.736
source is, my usual analogy is about
a chocolate cheesecake, right? Um,

00:37:09.176 --> 00:37:12.776
usually for you, when you want to buy your
cheesecake, you go to a bakery, they give you the

00:37:12.936 --> 00:37:16.576
cheesecake. The other one way of
having a cheesecake is have your

00:37:16.616 --> 00:37:20.576
grandma give you a recipe of how to
make that. When we do open source,

00:37:20.936 --> 00:37:24.656
we give you the chocolate cake,
and we give you the recipe to

00:37:24.736 --> 00:37:28.646
actually remake the same cake,
but at the same time tell you how

00:37:28.676 --> 00:37:32.516
to build the oven and also
how you're allowed to modify

00:37:32.636 --> 00:37:35.536
the recipe and resell it to someone else.

00:37:35.576 --> 00:37:39.076
And this is because software is
just a very long recipe of small

00:37:39.116 --> 00:37:42.996
instruction. Computers are not
very clever. They go very, very

00:37:43.016 --> 00:37:46.616
fast. So a normal program has
tens of billions of instructions

00:37:46.976 --> 00:37:49.856
instead of the tens when you
have your chocolate recipe. So

00:37:50.836 --> 00:37:54.826
a lot of the software industry was
about selling software, like where you

00:37:54.876 --> 00:37:58.776
just have like the final
cheesecake. In open source, we

00:37:58.796 --> 00:38:02.616
give you everything, and
that managed to get a

00:38:02.656 --> 00:38:06.316
lot of people work together, right? Because
then you decide that you're going to

00:38:06.356 --> 00:38:10.316
make the best program, the best
recipe for video, and you create

00:38:10.416 --> 00:38:14.796
communities. In FFmpeg, since the
beginning of FFmpeg, probably

00:38:15.756 --> 00:38:17.076
two thousand to three thousand-

00:38:17.116 --> 00:38:17.126
- In the thousands, yeah

00:38:17.126 --> 00:38:21.036
- ... people have contributed from the beginning,
right? And then it's exactly like the

00:38:21.076 --> 00:38:24.736
Linux kernel, right? The Linux kernel
has probably ten thousand people

00:38:24.756 --> 00:38:28.466
contributing everywhere, and
they get together, well,

00:38:28.516 --> 00:38:32.396
mostly online, right? So they
virtually get together to create the

00:38:32.416 --> 00:38:37.005
best tool for something. And on
FFmpeg and VLC, it's just like,

00:38:38.556 --> 00:38:42.426
well, this codec doesn't work, so I'm
going to work on the codec, and I'm going

00:38:42.496 --> 00:38:46.256
to add the support for this file
inside FFmpeg, so it will be

00:38:46.756 --> 00:38:50.716
beneficial to everyone. Because again, we
work for the greater good. We work for

00:38:51.316 --> 00:38:54.016
everyone, and that is what open source is.

00:38:54.596 --> 00:38:57.076
- And we should mention,
