- The license is a social contract
in terms of Rousseau de

00:39:53.376 --> 00:39:57.056
facto of the community. The community does

00:39:57.116 --> 00:40:01.036
not agree on much beside
the license. People go

00:40:01.116 --> 00:40:04.956
around, discuss around because
of the license, and that

00:40:05.036 --> 00:40:09.016
also allow those license fork, right?
Sometimes the community splits, but

00:40:09.116 --> 00:40:11.916
it's possible because of the
license and to merge back.

00:40:12.066 --> 00:40:15.356
And we've seen that so many
times, right? GCC and GC,

00:40:15.856 --> 00:40:19.556
And EGCS in the past. We have
seen, for example, all the web

00:40:19.616 --> 00:40:23.536
browsers, right? They started as web,
like KHTML, which becomes WebKit and

00:40:23.576 --> 00:40:26.436
then which becomes Blink,
