02:00:11.776 --> 02:00:15.736
you can't process 10-bit data
natively on a CPU. So that means you

02:00:15.776 --> 02:00:19.676
have to stick it in 16
bits. So that means you

02:00:19.716 --> 02:00:23.695
have six wasted bits. So there's different
packing formats to actually pack

02:00:23.736 --> 02:00:26.396
the data more efficiently because
when you send that over a network,

02:00:27.276 --> 02:00:31.256
you lose... 'Cause you need to
save that 40%. For example, on PCI

02:00:31.316 --> 02:00:35.256
Express, you may only have bus bandwidth
to do that. And so I think internally we

02:00:35.276 --> 02:00:38.996
have about... Some are industry
ones and some are internal to our

02:00:39.056 --> 02:00:45.186
own hardware that we build. We have a,
