a constant bit rate.

02:56:11.884 --> 02:56:15.394
There was a lot of optimization,
mostly by Loren also, um-

02:56:15.774 --> 02:56:19.424
... on anime, right? For a long
time, anime was very badly

02:56:19.484 --> 02:56:23.344
encoded because there was a ton of
banding, right? And so you see those

02:56:23.844 --> 02:56:26.964
those issues, and there
was a ton of things. So

02:56:27.204 --> 02:56:31.024
x264 is, like-- And today
it's still the reference

02:56:31.104 --> 02:56:38.354
to any encoder, new encoder, AV1, AV2,
VVC, HEVC, everyone compares to x264.

02:56:38.684 --> 02:56:42.084
- One of my favorite films, Cinema
Paradiso, I know the engineer

02:56:42.144 --> 02:56:46.024
