02:58:45.565 --> 02:58:49.385
And so all of that was
handcrafted, and it fits the open

02:58:49.456 --> 02:58:53.356
source community, right? Because they
needed tools to encode, to do fan subbing,

02:58:53.396 --> 02:58:57.096
right? One of the most amazing open
source projects for subtitles is called

02:58:57.176 --> 02:59:00.956
Aegisub, and it's a subtitle... It's

02:59:00.996 --> 02:59:06.496
done for anime, for, for South
Asian and Japanese languages.

02:59:06.956 --> 02:59:09.836
- There are weird textures in
